            "samples": {
                "band7": "I'm going to talk about my high school teacher, Mr. Nam. He taught me Mathematics for three years. He influenced me because he was always very patient and encouraged me to work hard, even when I found the subjects difficult. Because of him, I became more confident and started to enjoy solving problems. He showed me that with persistence, I can achieve anything. His influence is significant because it helped me choose my career path in engineering.",
                "band8": "I’d like to describe my grandfather, who has been a profound influence on my life and personal development. I’ve known him since my earliest childhood, of course, and he has always been a pillar of wisdom in our family. He influenced me by instilling a strong work ethic and a deep sense of integrity through his own actions. I particularly admire his resilience during difficult times. His influence is significant because it has shaped my core values and provided me with a moral compass that guides my decisions today.",
                "band9": "The individual who has exerted the most significant influence on my life is undoubtedly my mentor, Dr. Elena, whom I met during my undergraduate studies. She has been a guiding light, not just in my academic pursuits but also in my broader understanding of social responsibility. Her influence was transformative; she challenged my preconceived notions and encouraged me to embrace intellectual curiosity. The significance of her influence lies in the way she empowered the development of my critical thinking skills and fostered a resilient mindset. She taught me that true leadership is founded on empathy and evidence-based decision-making, which has fundamentally reshaped my life’s trajectory."
            },
